JOHANNESBURG - The African National Congress held a media briefing at Luthuli House on Tuesday afternoon to communicate the outcomes of its extended National Executive Committee meeting. In an unprecedented move a motion of no confidence in President Jacob Zuma was tabled by NEC member and Tourism Minister Derek Hanekom on Saturday, resulting in the gathering going into extra time. ANC secretary general Gwede Mantashe held the briefing, ultimately announcing that the NEC did not support the call for President Zuma to resign. READ: Four senior ANC members rally for Zuma's recall The motion was said to have divided members of the executive, with Health Minister Aaron Motsoaledi and Public Works Minister Thulas Nxesi arguing in favour of Zuma's removal. International Relations Minister Maite Nkoane Mashabane, State Security Minister David Mahlobo and Agricultural Minister and SACP chair, Senzeni Zokwana supporting the president's stay. eNCA